## **6. Mathematical Abstraction**

Let:

* ( A_t ) = attractor vector at time ( t )
* ( S_t ) = system state
* ( I ) = set of invariants
* ( C ) = set of coherence decisions

Define the Ledger as:

[
CL = { (c, i, A_t, \Delta S) \mid c \in C, i \in I }
]

Where each entry contributes to:

[
S_{t+1} = S_t + f(CL_t)
]

And the stability condition:

[
||A_{t+1} - A_t|| \rightarrow \min
]

The Ledger therefore acts as a meta-stabilizer on attractor drift.

